Mike S wrote:
> 1/2. This is easy to visualize if you just consider one cylinder. 
> Being a 4 stroke engine, that cylinder fires once every two 
> revolutions, so the distributor "points" to that cylinder every two 
> revolutions.
while it may seem obvious, just wanted to mention that the rotor 
"points" at the cylinder('s wire) every two revolutions of the *crank* - 
rotor only makes one full revolution.  It just sounded like every two 
revolutions of the distributor...

